      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely slice your <strong>ginger</strong>, then chop into matchsticks as finely as you can</p><p>Combine your <strong>black bean paste</strong> with 25ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[35ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[50ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>black bean sauce</strong></p>",
