      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add your<strong> basa fillet[s]</strong> to a plate and drizzle your <strong>soy sauce</strong> all over</p><p>Turn the <strong>basa</strong> several times until the soy sauce fully soaks into the fish</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>cornflour </strong>all over and rub it into both sides of the fish until fully coated, then set aside for later</p><p>Tip: Coat the fish in the cornflour one side at a time to avoid stickiness!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614615045373-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614615045373-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614615045373-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614615045373-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614615045373-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 paper (or two!) and to a baking tray</p><p>Lay the <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sliced ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in the middle with your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>black bean sauce</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the vegetables to form a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>sealed parcel[s], then put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until tender – these are your <strong>black bean greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614615069298-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614615069298-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614615069298-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614615069298-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614615069298-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining sliced ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until crispy</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once crispy, transfer to a bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>crispy ginger & garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614615140927-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614615140927-x400.jpg",
